<img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/868/62/28686215.jpg" ></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvinarruinthang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vinar Ruinthang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/10/01 9:19:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: umm.</span><hr size=1> All good points but at 55+ lvls diamond skin is nice but shouldnt be necessary.  If you have your epic you SHOULD know how to not overburn and you will never get hit.  The only damage that kills us is magical and diamondskin does nothing to protect against that.  dont get me wrong for soloing that is great it takes what 400 damage absorbed.  thats nice.  Arent we working to get away from soloing though.  just seems funny that one proc from a SK weapon kills a wiz no matter what (if only using wiz self only buffs) just cuts through the diamond skin like nothing.  <br>
<br>
well at least we will be shiny when we go down.  When i go for it.  It will be for the stats on the staff and trying to do something epic.  Good luck to you all on yours<br>
