Dread Overlord of the Violent Harvest</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/17/01 11:28:27 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: umm.</span><hr size=1> They letting Inkies do Epics? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
/rude Verant <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Seriously, though, Epics are supposed to make one better at what they do. Like you said, Vinar, Wizards at your level should not be melleeing. As such, a healthy weapon proc is useless. Stats to increase the Mana Pool and decrease Fizzles and Interrupts are far from useless to a Wizard.<br>
<br>
Conversly, a SK needs to deal out damage with their weapon, so the proc is very usefull. Same goes for the Paladin Epic. Some say that there are two better weapons for Pallies over the final version of our epic. However, these do not proc (FD 155dam proc) and do not have the Stat Modifiers (+20Str, +10Sta, +15Wis, +10 Sv. Magik/Cold/Fire/Poisen/Disease, +70HP, +30Mana) of the Epic. People need to be reminded that there is more to a weapon than Dam/Sec that needs to be examined.<br>
